# Mermaid spacing in docs

When writing or editing `docs/**/*.mdx`, add **`<br/>`** on its own line immediately after every ` ```mermaid ` closing fence.

Reference: `docs/frameworks/gain-mcp.mdx`, `docs/blueprints/router-blueprint.mdx`.

## Required pattern (bare mermaid)

1. Open with a ` ```mermaid ` fenced block and close it with ` ``` `.
2. On the **next line**, add `<br/>`.
3. Then the heading, paragraph, or table.

Example shape (closing fence, then spacer, then prose):

    [mermaid fence open]
    flowchart LR
        A --> B
    [mermaid fence close]
    <br/>
    ## Next section

## Wrapped in `gain-mermaid` (framework pages)

When the fence is inside `<div className="gain-mermaid">`, put `<br/>` after `</div>`:

    <br/>
    <div className="gain-mermaid">
    [mermaid fence + diagram]
    </div>
    <br/>

Optional `<br/>` before the wrapper is fine for top spacing. **After** the diagram is required.

## Do not add

- `<br/>` inside the mermaid fence (breaks the diagram).
- Duplicate `<br/>` between consecutive diagrams unless prose sits between them.

## Before finishing

1. Every ` ```mermaid ` block in changed `.mdx` files has `<br/>` after the closing fence (or after `</div>` when wrapped).
2. When editing a section with mermaid, fix spacing on blocks you touch; do not bulk-rewrite unrelated diagrams.
